    dc:creator "Souma, Jun; Ishikawa, Tadashi" ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "A taxonomic review of the genus Physopelta (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Largidae) from Japan, Korea, and Taiwan, with a new record of Ph. parviceps from China" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4668176>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4668179>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4668213> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4668176>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Habitus images of four Physopelta (Neophysopelta) species, dorsal view: Ph. (N.) gutta gutta, male (A) and female (B) from Japan proper; Ph. (N.) fusciscutellata sp. nov., male from the main island of Taiwan (C) and female from the Ryukyu Islands, Japan (D); Ph. (N.) quadriguttata, male (E, G) and female (F) from the main island of Taiwan; Ph. (N.) lutaspidata sp. nov., male from the main island of Taiwan (H). Arrows mark antenna with antennomeral oligomery and malformed calli. Scale bar: 5.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4668176/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4668179>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Habitus images of Physopelta (Neophysopelta) parviceps, dorsal view: macropterous male (A) and female (B) from Japan proper; macropterous male (C, E) and female (D, F) from the Ryukyu Islands, Japan; brachypterous male (G) and female (H) from Japan proper. Arrows mark antennae with antennomeral oligomery. Scale bar: 5.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4668179/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4668213>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. A number of individuals of Physopelta (Neophysopelta) quadriguttata from the main island of Taiwan attracted to artificial light." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4668213/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

